Actually, in react-i18next the `{{ variable }}` syntax in `<Trans>` children has always been a special pattern. Let me check if this is a typing issue with the `<span>` element specifically:

The `<span>` children type is `ReactNode`, and `{{ name }}` creates an object `{ name: "..." }` which isn't valid `ReactNode`. This worked before because older React/TS types were more lenient. The fix is to use `values` prop on `<Trans>`:
